Edit a Cross Filter

To change how a cross filter filters the primary or secondary object, edit it.

Required Editions and User Permissions
Available in: both Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience
Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions
Enhanced Folder Sharing

User Permissions Needed
Enhanced Folder Sharing
Create and Customize Reports

Report Builder OR Report Builder (Lightning Experience)

To add edit, or delete a cross filter in private reports:	Enhanced Folder Sharing
To add edit, or delete a cross filter in private and public reports:	Enhanced Folder Sharing

The steps for editing a cross filter are a little different depending on whether youâ€™re using Lightning Experience or Salesforce Classic.

Edit a Cross Filter in the Lightning Experience Report Builder
Edit a report.
From the FILTERS tab, under Cross Filters, find the cross filter you want to edit.
Click the cross filter.
Show Me dropdown, change the primary object.
Operator dropdown, choose whether to show your primary object with or without a secondary object. Then, choose the secondary object.
Secondary Object dropdown, change the secondary object.
Apply.

To edit a subfilter on the secondary object, click the sub filter.
Edit Filter menu, change operator and values.
Remove the subfilter by clicking X. Then, add another subfilter based on the desired field.
Apply.
Save the report, click Save.

Edit a Cross Filter in the Salesforce Classic Report Builder
Edit a report.
Filters pane, click find the cross filter you want to edit. Click Edit.
Change primary object, operator, or secondary object.
Edit subfilters by changing field, operator, and value.
Remove.
Add Secondary Object Filter, where Secondary Object is the name of the secondary object.
Click OK.
Save the report, click Save.

The report filters based on the primary-secondary object relationship and any additional filters on the secondary object.
